<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="354" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1352,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1352,1379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2020" box="[330,866,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jirofti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[330,553,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Empidideicus jirofti</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[874,965,1353,1379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[874,965,1353,1379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is differentiated from all other species of the genus from 
<collectingCountry box="[326,371,1389,1415]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Iran</collectingCountry>
by the combination of following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1352,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Frons yellow with a quadrate brown spot below ocellus, occiput brown with a small yellow spot; mesonotum brown with two admedian yellow stripes; scutellum brown with yellowish tinge basomedially; furca U-shaped with two process on lateral arms; reservoir globular with shallow invagination; gonocoxae with two triangular plate including perpendicular pointed process.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="359" pageId="2" pageNumber="354" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1352,2027]" box="[199,1073,1568,1595]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1568,1595]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<figureCitation box="[424,506,1569,1595]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.adult habitus: a. male paratype, b. female paratype,c. female type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609593/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). Lengths: Body: 
<quantity box="[707,845,1569,1595]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="354" unit="mm" value="1.1" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.3 mm</quantity>
. Wing: 
<quantity box="[931,1069,1569,1595]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="354" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1352,2027]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1605,1631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[271,337,1605,1632]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.adult habitus: a. male paratype, b. female paratype,c. female type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609593/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
a–b). Head ovoid, longer than high; eyes dichoptic, separated at vertex by about 1.6 times between lateral ocelli; vertex blackish brown; occiput blackish brown, with tiny yellow spot in upper half; frons slightly depressed medially, yellow with quadrate brown spot just below median ocellus; antennae set in deep pocket; Scape yellow, subrectangular, wider than long, Pedicel yellow, subglobular, slightly wider than long, first flagellomere light brown, elliptical, length two-time greatest width, about three times (3.2) second flagellomere in length, second flagellomere light brown, cylindrical, apically with tiny hyaline stylus (
<figureCitation box="[950,1024,1785,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1282,1307]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1263]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1437,174,1263]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. antenna, b. right wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609591/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Fig.1a</figureCitation>
); face yellow; mentum yellow medially brown laterally; labrum stiff, pointed apically, brown, about 1.2 head high in length; labium brown, 1.7 head high in length, pointed apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[528,617,1857,1883]" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[635,704,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.adult habitus: a. male paratype, b. female paratype,c. female type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609593/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="354">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
a–c). Mesonotum completely brown with two admedian yellow stripes coming from anterior margin of mesonotum to level of postalar calli; postpronotal lobe, postalar calli, lateral margin from postpronotal to postalar calli yellow; prescutellar area completely blackish brown; scutellum brown medially with yellowish tinge; pleura predominantly dark brown except following: upper margins of katepisternum and meron and dorsolateral corner of anepisternum and posterior margin of anepimeron; halter stem and knob white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[229,285,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Legs</emphasis>
. Femora brown, distally narrowly yellow; tibia yellow; two basal segment of tarsi yellow, remainder brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,302,188,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[318,400,189,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1282,1307]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1263]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1437,174,1263]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. antenna, b. right wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609591/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, costa ends slightly beyond vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[906,932,206,220]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">4+5</subScript>
, Sc ends much before costa; br and bm cells confluent, discal cell absent, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[503,511,242,256]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">1</subScript>
curve; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[622,630,242,256]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">2</subScript>
straight; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[762,787,242,256]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">1+2</subScript>
0.7 times M 
<quantity box="[930,968,225,256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="5" pageNumber="357" unit="in" value="2.0">
<subScript attach="left" box="[930,938,242,256]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">2</subScript>
in
</quantity>
length; anal cell open for width subequal to r-m cross vein; veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[451,459,278,292]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[499,507,278,292]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">2</subScript>
,Cua 
<subScript attach="left" box="[560,568,278,292]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">1</subScript>
translucent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,831,260,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites almost brown, posterior and lateral margins narrowly yellow; sternites brown, posterior margins narrowly yellow; pleura completely white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1208,1377,296,323]" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov. male genitalia: a. phallic complex, b. epandrium, c. gonocoxites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[328,409,333,360]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov. male genitalia: a. phallic complex, b. epandrium, c. gonocoxites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, laterally with two processes; cercus triangular, large; gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1427,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov. male genitalia: a. phallic complex, b. epandrium, c. gonocoxites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
) connected narrowly medially, subtriangular in dorsal view, apical margin round less sclerotized than other parts, with two sclerotized triangular plates including perpendicular pointed spike, medially with narrow apically curved sclerotized appendage; gonostyli subtrapezoidal with round margin including long bristles; distiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1434,196,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov. male genitalia: a. phallic complex, b. epandrium, c. gonocoxites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="357">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
) wide, short, lateral aedeagal apodeme slightly curved, longer than tumefied basiphallus; apical aedeagal apodeme large with two large rectangular rami basally.
</paragraph>
