<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[305,375,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[396,1191,174,1994]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.adult habitus: a. male paratype, b. female paratype,c. female type." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609593/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
b–c). Similar to male except larger in size and with larger yellow spot on lateral margin of occiput and pleural sclerites lighter. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[571,771,188,215]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[789,861,188,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. female genitalia, b. spermathecal reservoirs, c. furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609597/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Furca U-shaped, lateral arms with two inwardly directed processes subapically (
<figureCitation box="[508,592,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. female genitalia, b. spermathecal reservoirs, c. furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609597/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); common spermathecal duct absent; basal spermathecal duct (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1385,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. female genitalia, b. spermathecal reservoirs, c. furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609597/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
) 1.2 times apical duct in length, striated, membranous, slightly widening distally, one tenth of apical part cylindrical, narrow, smooth; apical spermathecal duct narrower than basal duct, tubular, smooth, spermathecal reservoir (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,2014,2039]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1407,553,1994]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov.: a. female genitalia, b. spermathecal reservoirs, c. furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609597/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) globular with shallow, cylindrical invagination, depth of invagination one tenth dimeter of reservoir.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="359" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,369,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1907" box="[607,759,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,759,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Empidideicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[944,989,369,395]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Iran</collectingCountry>
have been recently keyed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gharali, B. &amp; Majnon Jahromi, B. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Fallahzadeh, M." pageId="7" pageNumber="359" pagination="27 - 34" refId="ref3965" refString="Gharali, B., Majnon Jahromi, B., Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Fallahzadeh, M. (2014) First record of the genus Empidideicus Becker (Diptera: Mythicomyiidae, Empidideicinae) from southern Iran with description of a new species, Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 151, 27 - 34." type="journal article" year="2014">
Gharali 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
. This new species is stymied at couplet 3 because the lateral margin of occiput is not completely yellow or black. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2020" box="[257,788,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jirofti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[257,480,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Empidideicus jirofti</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,885,441,467]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[795,885,441,467]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is easily separated from the other species by this character.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="359" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,512,539]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Distribution.</emphasis>
The new species is currently known only from Jiroft city (
<collectingRegion box="[1009,1208,512,539]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Kerman province</collectingRegion>
) in the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[1391,1436,513,539]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,228,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1997,2022]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[403,1184,171,1975]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitat of Empidideicus. jirofti sp. nov. in Jiroft City." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3689300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3689300/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[301,349,549,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">type</typeStatus>
locality is a mountainous place covered with plants of the families 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1112,1255,548,574]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rhamnaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1272,1367,548,574]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Ziziphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1367,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Ziziphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.), 
<taxonomicName box="[151,255,584,610]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[272,393,584,610]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,393,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Astragalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.), and 
<taxonomicName box="[517,644,584,610]" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Gramineae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="359" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,621,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2020" box="[633,1159,620,647]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jirofti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[633,854,620,647]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Empidideicus jirofti</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1165,1261,621,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1165,1255,621,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="359" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
is derived from the word Jiroft, a city in the southern 
<collectingRegion box="[576,774,656,683]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Kerman province</collectingRegion>
, an area of about 18 square kilometers with hot and humid climate, so this city is called the greenhouse city of 
<collectingCountry box="[731,780,693,719]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="359">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
